Description: Use ntpwait -q
 The -q option makes ntpwait less strict.  We do not need full synchronization
 before time-sync.target.  The goal is to ensure that the time is close, but
 most importantly, not going to move backwards.  (This is all that is provided
 by systemd-timesyncd, for example.)  The initial stepping of the clock is
 sufficient.  This change can mean the difference of many minutes in delay.
Forwarded: not-needed
Origin: vendor
Author: Richard Laager <rlaager@wiktel.com>
